
Overview of noun task

The noun task has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (18) undertaking, project, task, labor -- (any piece of work that is undertaken or attempted; "he prepared for great undertakings")
2. (15) job, task, chore -- (a specific piece of work required to be done as a duty or for a specific fee; "estimates of the city's loss on that job ranged as high as a million dollars"; "the job of repairing the engine took several hours"; "the endless task of classifying the samples"; "the farmer's morning chores")

Overview of verb task

The verb task has 2 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                         
1. task -- (assign a task to; "I tasked him with looking after the children")
2. tax, task -- (use to the limit; "you are taxing my patience")
